{"type":"text","timestamp":1773440179268,"sessionID":"ses_316bba7bfffeeA1IqckNkl9JmJ","part":{"id":"prt_ce944d034001hErCigrtiGSQUR","sessionID":"ses_316bba7bfffeeA1IqckNkl9JmJ","messageID":"msg_ce944c2c7001NTZZQHCswBQae8","type":"text","text":"---\n## Goal\n\nImplement a \"dynamic agent types\" feature for the wombo-combo (woco) AI agent orchestration system. The feature allows users to specify different agent types per task, with agent definitions dynamically pulled from the `msitarzewski/agency-agents` GitHub repository and converted to woco-compatible agent definitions (markdown files in `.opencode/agents/`). Users can specify agent types via the `agent` YAML field on tasks or the `--agent` CLI flag.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Must pull agent definitions from the agency-agents GitHub repo dynamically (not bundled statically)\n- Must convert/adapt agency-agents format to woco's agent template format\n- Must cache pulled agents locally in `.wombo-combo/agents-cache/` (separate from `.opencode/agents/` which is the active install dir)\n- Must support per-task agent type selection (via task YAML `agent` field or `--agent` flag)\n- Must support offline mode with cached agents\n- Fallback behavior: if agent not found, emit warning and fall back to `generalist-agent.md`; if registry unreachable, use only locally cached agents\n- After completing all changes, run `bun run build` to verify\n- Use conventional commits with scope `dynamic-agent-types`\n- Do NOT push to remote or modify `tasks` directory\n- Use `portless run` when starting any server for testing\n- The worktree is at `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/dynamic-agent-types`\n\n## Discoveries\n\n**This feature is already substantially implemented.** After thorough code exploration, the following components already exist and are functional:\n\n1. **`src/lib/agent-registry.ts`** (567 lines) — Full implementation including:\n   - `resolveAgentForTask()` — resolves agent definition with cache check, fetch from registry, TTL-based cache validation, offline fallback\n   - `prepareAgentDefinitions()` — batch-resolves agents for all tasks in a wave\n   - `fetchAgent()` — fetches raw markdown from GitHub raw content URLs\n   - `listRegistryAgents()` — lists available agents via GitHub Contents API\n   - `getCachedAgents()` — lists locally cached agents\n   - `cacheAgent()` / `getCachedAgent()` — cache read/write operations\n   - `writeAgentToWorktree()` — writes patched agent into worktree's `.opencode/agents/`\n   - `isSpecializedAgent()` — type guard for resolved agents\n   - `AgentResolution`, `ResolvedAgent`, `GeneralistFallback` types\n\n2. **`src/lib/format-converter.ts`** (410 lines) — Full agency-agents → woco format conversion:\n   - `isAgencyAgentFormat()` — detects agency-agents format via frontmatter heuristics\n   - `parseAgencyAgent()` — parses agency-agents markdown structure\n   - `convertAgencyToWoco()` — converts to woco-compatible format\n   - `normalizeAgentFormat()` — convenience detect+convert entry point\n\n3. **`src/lib/templates.ts`** (433 lines) — Agent template rendering and patching:\n   - `patchImportedAgent()` — patches imported agents with woco operational context (calls `normalizeAgentFormat()` automatically)\n   - `renderGeneralistAgent()` — renders the standalone generalist agent\n   - `ensureAgentDefinition()` — ensures agent definition exists before launch\n\n4. **`src/config.ts`** — Config already has `agentRegistry` section with `mode`, `source`, `cacheDir`, `cacheTTL`\n\n5. **`src/lib/tasks.ts`** — Task type already has `agent_type?: string` and `agent?: string` fields\n\n6. **`src/lib/state.ts`** — AgentState already has `agent_name` and `agent_type` fields\n\n7. **`src/commands/launch.ts`** — Already integrates agent registry:\n   - Calls `prepareAgentDefinitions()` before launching\n   - Passes `agentResolutions` through launch pipeline\n   - `launchSingleHeadless()` writes specialized agents to worktrees\n   - `launchHeadless()` in `launcher.ts` uses `agentName` parameter\n\n8. **`src/index.ts`** — CLI already has `--agent` flag support\n\n9. **`src/lib/launcher.ts`** — `LaunchOptions` already has `agentName` field, `launchHeadless()` passes it to the agent binary\n\n## Accomplished\n\n**The feature appears to be fully implemented already.** All the core components exist:\n- ✅ Dynamic pulling from agency-agents GitHub repo\n- ✅ Format conversion (agency-agents → woco format)\n- ✅ Local caching in `.wombo-combo/agents-cache/`\n- ✅ Per-task agent type selection via `agent_type` field\n- ✅ CLI `--agent` flag support\n- ✅ Offline mode with cached agents\n- ✅ Fallback to generalist agent on failure\n- ✅ TTL-based cache invalidation\n- ✅ Integration into launch pipeline (both headless and interactive)\n\n**What needs to be done:**\n1. **Verify the build passes** — Run `bun run build` to confirm everything compiles\n2. **Check for any gaps** — There may be subtle integration gaps (e.g., does the `agent` field from task YAML get properly mapped to `agent_name` in state creation? Does `--agent` CLI flag override per-task agents correctly?)\n3. **Review the `createAgentState` and `createWaveState` functions** in `state.ts` (only first 100 lines were read) to verify `agent_name` and `agent_type` are properly populated during wave creation\n4. **Check the rest of `launch.ts`** (only first 1420 lines were read, file is longer) — specifically the `cmdLaunch` function to see how `prepareAgentDefinitions` is called and how agent resolutions flow into wave state creation\n5. **Run the build** and fix any issues\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n### Core implementation files (already exist):\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/dynamic-agent-types/src/lib/agent-registry.ts` — Agent registry fetch, cache, resolve (READ, 567 lines)\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/dynamic-agent-types/src/lib/format-converter.ts` — Agency-agents → woco format conversion (READ, 410 lines)\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/dynamic-agent-types/src/lib/templates.ts` — Agent template rendering and patching (READ, 433 lines)\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/dynamic-agent-types/src/lib/launcher.ts` — Process spawning with agent name support (READ, 412 lines)\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/dynamic-agent-types/src/lib/tasks.ts` — Task types with `agent_type` and `agent` fields (READ, 661 lines)\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/dynamic-agent-types/src/lib/state.ts` — Wave state with `agent_name` and `agent_type` (READ first 100 lines, needs more)\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/dynamic-agent-types/src/commands/launch.ts` — Launch command with agent registry integration (READ first 1420 lines, needs more)\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/dynamic-agent-types/src/config.ts` — Config with `agentRegistry` section (READ, 362 lines)\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/dynamic-agent-types/src/index.ts` — CLI entry point with `--agent` flag (READ, 1016 lines)\n\n### Template files:\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/dynamic-agent-types/src/templates/` — Directory containing agent templates\n\n### Config/build:\n- `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/dynamic-agent-types/package.json` — Build script: `bun build src/index.ts --outdir dist --target node`\n\n### Files still needing review:\n- `src/lib/state.ts` — lines 101+ (need to check `createAgentState` and `createWaveState`)\n- `src/commands/launch.ts` — lines 1421+ (need to check `cmdLaunch` agent resolution flow)\n- `src/commands/resume.ts` — may need agent registry integration for resumed waves\n- `src/lib/preflight.ts` — imported in launch.ts, may be relevant\n---","time":{"start":1773440179267,"end":1773440179267}}}
