{"type":"text","timestamp":1773440622189,"sessionID":"ses_316bba7bfffeeA1IqckNkl9JmJ","part":{"id":"prt_ce94c2bd9001VCNc4iJGIJYeqo","sessionID":"ses_316bba7bfffeeA1IqckNkl9JmJ","messageID":"msg_ce94c2378001O1Rnwb2GOZNW6H","type":"text","text":"Everything is complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Feature Status: Complete\n\nThe **dynamic agent types** feature was already substantially implemented across the codebase from prior work (the `feature/agent-selection-per-feature` branch merged into main). All core components were in place:\n\n- ✅ **Agent Registry** (`src/lib/agent-registry.ts`) — fetches from `msitarzewski/agency-agents` GitHub repo, caches in `.wombo-combo/agents-cache/`, TTL-based validation, offline fallback\n- ✅ **Format Converter** (`src/lib/format-converter.ts`) — converts agency-agents markdown format to woco-compatible agent definitions\n- ✅ **Template Patching** (`src/lib/templates.ts`) — patches imported agents with woco operational context\n- ✅ **Per-task agent selection** — `agent_type` and `agent` fields on tasks, `--agent` CLI flag\n- ✅ **Launch integration** — `prepareAgentDefinitions()` called before launch, resolutions passed through pipeline\n- ✅ **Preflight UI** (`src/lib/preflight.ts`) — console and TUI confirmation for specialized agent assignments\n\n### Gaps Found and Fixed\n\nThree integration gaps were identified and fixed in one commit:\n\n1. **`launchInteractive()` didn't pass `--agent` flag** — The headless launcher passed `--agent` to the agent binary, but the interactive (multiplexer) launcher silently ignored the `agentName` option. Fixed by adding `--agent` to the command arguments in `src/lib/launcher.ts`.\n\n2. **`resume.ts` didn't re-resolve agents from registry** — When relaunching agents during resume, specialized agent definitions weren't re-resolved from the registry or re-written to the worktree. Fixed by adding agent resolution logic before relaunching, writing agent definitions to worktrees, and passing `agentName` to interactive launches and `agentResolutions` to headless launches.\n\n3. **`retry.ts` didn't re-resolve agents from registry** — Same gap as resume. Fixed with the same pattern: resolve from registry, write to worktree, pass to launcher.\n\n### Build Verification\n- ✅ TypeScript typecheck passes\n- ✅ Build passes (1.0 MB bundle, 157 modules)","time":{"start":1773440622188,"end":1773440622188}}}
